Plates
22. Howardena Pindell. Untitled
#87b. 1977. Cut-and-pasted and
painted punched paper, acrylic,
watercolor, thread, mat board,
sprayed adhesive, and string on
paper, 22% x 26 in. (56.2 x 66 cm)
Work contemporaneous with that
featured in Pindell's exhibition
Recent Works with Paper and Video
Drawings (1977); sold by JAM to
the Metropolitan Museum of Art
23-30. Dawoud Bey. Photographs
of A Book Party for Contextures,
which took place on the same
day as the opening of Houston
Conwill's exhibition Notes of
a Griot. March 18, 1978.
Pictured (left to right, top to
bottom): Melvin Edwards, Bill
Hutson, and James Little; Lowery
Stokes Sims and Marquita Pool-
Eckert; Houston Conwill (left).
and Linda Goode Bryant (center);
James Little (left); Richard
Powell and Gylbert Coker;
Houston Conwill, David Hammons,
and Randy Williams; Marcy S.
Philips and Linda Goode Bryant;
Reggie Jackson, Camille Billops,
